        <abstract> 
<p>Sends his work discussing the anatomical seat of the faculty of language [<hi rend="italic">On aphasia</hi> (1870)]. Concludes that it may be impossible to find any cerebral centre for speech and that this fact opposes the idea of the descent of man from some lower form.</p> 
        </abstract>
